(1, 1, 'Sunshine Coast Trail', 'Located in the Powell River area, Canadas longest hut-to-hut hiking trail. It stretches over 180km that range from coastal shorelines and old growth forests to pristine lakes and panoramic mountaintops.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/287240/pexels-photo-287240.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=500&h=500&dpr=1', '-124.1367', '49.8114'),

(1, 1, 'Al Habrichs Ridge Trail', 'Taking around 5-6 hours to hike, as the walk leads you out near the majestic Neverland Lake The route goes just beyond Neverland Lake and an extended route can be hiked to Neverland Falls. The Als Habrich Ridge Trail is best done by taking the Sea To Sky gondola to the top but can also be done after hiking the Sea To Summit route from the bottom of the gondola.', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/56760/pexels-photo-56760.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=500&h=500&dpr=1', '-123.115239', '49.676976'),

(1, 1, 'Black Tusk Trail', 'The dark, jagged edges of Black Tusk make it one of the most scenic and unique hikes in southwestern British Columbia. Black Tusk is the most spectacular mountain in the area, and one of the most difficult terrain, with 29 km round trip. and elevation gain of 1740 meters. ', 'https://images.pexels.com/photos/868097/pexels-photo-868097.jpeg?auto=compress&cs=tinysrgb&w=500&h=500&dpr=1', '-123.042753', '49.9751162'),

(1, 1, 'Elfin Lakes', 'Two lakes in Garibaldi Provincial Park that are popular for hiking, snowshoeing, skiing, and mountain bicycling trail located east of Squamish, British Columbia, Canada.', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1c/ElfinPano.jpg', '-122.4762', '50.3413'),

(1, 1, 'Joffre Lakes', 'A provincial park located 35 kilometres (22 mi) east of Pemberton in British Columbia, Canada. It was established in 1996, when Joffre Lakes Recreation Area (created 1988) was upgraded to park status. Three glacier-fed lakes are located in the park: Lower, Middle, and Upper Joffre Lakes. The rock flour in the water reflects blue and green waves, and gives the lakes a turquoise colour. Joffre Lakes is a popular destination for hikers in the summer and mountain climbers in the winter due to its scenic lakes, glaciers and challenging peaks.', 'https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8d/Upper_Joffre_Lake_-_British_Columbia%2C_Canada.jpg/1920px-Upper_Joffre_Lake_-_British_Columbia%2C_Canada.jpg', '-122.98824611814419', '49.787158149999996'),

